luation   interval of each horizontal well. The visible TVT_input column gives the known   interpreted TVT before the prediction start; after that point it becomes missing and we must infer the continuation.                                               This starter:                                                                      • Uses only fie\n1: Reading kernel: cdeotte/xgb-starter-cv-15\n5: ┃             XGBoost Starter - ROGII Wellbore Geology Prediction              ┃\n8: This notebook is a compact XGBoost starter for the ROGII - Wellbore Geology\n20: • Builds per-well context features from the known TVT_input segment.\n21: • Adds simple Typewell gamma-ray correlation features inspired by the\n23: • Uses well-grouped K-fold validation so rows from the same well do not leak\n48: from sklearn.model_selection import GroupKFold\n49: from xgboost import XGBRegressor\n70: \"eval_metric\": \"rmse\",\n94: Path(\"/kaggle/input/competitions/rogii-wellbore-geology-prediction\"),\n135: display(sample_sub.groupby(\"well_id\").size().rename(\"rows_to_predict\").reset_i\n141: 3. Feature Engineering\n149: 15.9 RMSE locally. XGBoost only needs to learn corrections away from that flat\n152: The slope-continuation values are still kept as features:\n164: def rmse(y_true, y_pred):\n209: return pd.DataFrame({\"TVT\": [], \"GR\": []})\n214: def build_features_for_well(horizontal_path, split=\"train\", test_row_map=None)\n237: # Very defensive fallback. This should not happen in the competition\n254: cur = h.loc[selected_idx, [\"MD\", \"X\", \"Y\", \"Z\", \"GR\", \"row_index\"]].copy()\n263: ps_gr = float(last_known.get(\"GR\", np.nan))\n274: cur[\"known_gr_mean\"] = known[\"GR\"].mean() if \"GR\" in known else np.nan\n275: cur[\"known_gr_std\"] = known[\"GR\"].std() if \"GR\" in known else np.nan\n276: cur[\"known_gr_min\"] = known[\"GR\"].min() if \"GR\" in known else np.nan\n277: cur[\"known_gr_max\"] = known[\"GR\"].max() if \"GR\" in known else np.nan\n278: cur[\"last_know